In her role as a high-powered City lawyer, Miriam Clegg does not often get the chance to play the everyday school mum. 

So it is little wonder she ended up looking surprisingly glamorous on a visit to a primary school yesterday – no doubt to the despair of regular mums everywhere.

The Deputy Prime Minister’s wife lit up the playground as she sashayed into Lairdsland Primary School in Glasgow flicking a perfectly coiffed mane and flashing a bright smile.

